(74305, 227901, 0, 1, 'ISLAND''S SUNRISE ', '「民主打入國際，世界包圍中央」--四月22日22點22分的國際英語版ISLAND''s SUNRISE 上線！\n\nCountdown: “Island’s Sunrise” New Version Debut on April 22, 22:22.（Please scroll down for English info)\n\n繼與滅火器合作的「島嶼天光」於youtube上線短短一周就突破100萬點閱率，企劃團隊構思推出全新「島嶼天光」國際英語版「 ISLAND''S SUNRISE」。\n\n不同於「島嶼天光」台語版歌詞聚焦太陽花學運，英文版歌詞改以「台灣追求民主過程」的故事為主軸，歌詞中提到“烈火般炙熱的呼吸，鑄造你的面具（Your face is cast with my breath, my heat）”便是隱喻鄭南榕為了信念不惜奉獻生命，經由許多人的努力，才有台灣目前民主的樣貌。而此英文歌詞是由藝術圈的數十位藝術家集思廣益，共同創作。\n\n透過網路號召，經過四月六號立院外徵選會的試唱後，敲定由獨立歌手鄭雙雙詮釋。並邀請曾以《翻滾吧！阿信》入圍金馬獎最佳配樂的王希文重新編曲製作，且由台北藝術大學新媒體藝術研究所師生協力拍攝回顧紀實。合力打造島嶼宏觀的學運精神。\n\n「島嶼天光」藝術組織表示，英語版的製作皆由視覺、音樂藝術工作者合力贊助參與，也簽署了島嶼天光藝術團隊共同契約，將同意於Bandcamp/INDIE VOX網路音樂平台開放免費下載與非營利再製版權。\n\nEarlier this month, the release of Taiwanese student movement theme song “ ISLAND''S SUNRISE” received a million hits within one week after its upload on youtube. Now the production team behind this amazing feat announces the release of an English version of “Island’s Sunrise” in hopes of reaching international audiences abroad. \n\nDifferent from its original Taiwanese lyrics, which focuses on the movement itself, the lyrics of this new version, collectively written by the Taiwanese artists organizing the project, shall address Taiwan’s past and current struggle for true democracy. For example, the lines “Your face is cast with my breath, my heat” is dedicated to Cheng, Nan-rung, the critic/human rights activist and a strong advocator of Taiwan’s independence, who sacrificed his life for the freedom of speech in an act of self-immolation. \n\nA call for audition for the singer of this new version was announced on the internet and subsequently took place outside the then occupied Legislative Yuan. Among countless talents, the independent singer 鄭雙雙 (Sherry Cheng) was chosen. The entire song was reproduced and arranged by 王希文 Owen Wang, whose work on the Taiwanese film “Jump Ashin!” was nominated by the Taipei Golden Horse Award for Best Original Score. Students and teachers from the Department of New Media Art of the Taipei National University of the Arts worked around the clock to document the final wrap-up of the student movement, which they shall incorporate into the new music video along with previous footage of the movement. The idea was to present the music video as a review of the entire student movement, from the beginning to the end. \n\nSince the English version of “Island’s Sunrise” is a result of collective artistic effort, the Island’s Sunrise team has issued a mutual agreement concerning the copyright properties of the work. The music platforms Bandcamp / INDIE VOX shall host the song as a free download,and it is open to the public for non-profit modification and adaptation.\n', '2014-04-22 00:00:00', 2000, 99, 1, 4, 'Colors grow and creep \n滋生的顏彩蔓延 \nMy tinted flesh outline your feet \n我以血肉之軀 描繪你的雙足 \nYour limbs , tightly we knit \n牢固地編織 你的肢臂 \nYour face is cast with my breath, and my heat \n烈火般炙熱的呼吸 鑄造你的面具\n\nThe hunters start to seize \n貪婪的人們見獵心喜 \nWe''re lost at sea, adrift like leaves \n我們在汪洋中迷失 像不知歸途的落葉 \nHave our hollers reached your heels? \n吶喊化作遠浪 可曾襲捲至你的踝邊 \nWe hope our whispers slightly touched your crown. \n但願我們的低語 輕觸過你的虛妄之冠\n\nDarkness breaks apart\n天色漸漸明朗 \nHorizon lined with a hopeful crowd \n不放棄理想的人 勾勒出遠方的地平線 \nA voice echoes, beckons \n廻盪的聲浪 召喚 \nWave by the wings below the sun \n在陽光下鼓動著翅膀 \nDarkness breaks apart \n天色漸漸明朗 \nThe flags raise high wall breaks down \n正義之旗高舉 高牆倒下 \nLink my spirit to your heart\n緊緊連結我們的意志和我們的心 \nTogether we stand up proud \n我們驕傲地站出來\n\nSetting sail, don''t fear, sky crystal clear \n揚起風帆 無所畏懼 天空再度澄澈透明 \nThe heavy fog may slow me down \n沈重的迷霧使我卻步 \nHold that fire high above the wild \n仍要在荒蕪之處高舉野火 \nFight for the glorious day to come\n為了輝煌之日戰鬥\n\nDarkness breaks apart \n天色漸漸明朗 \nDarkness breaks apart\n黎明就在不遠的地方 \nWith pounding hearts we are making this start\n滿懷悸動 我們從這裡出發\n\nDarkness breaks apart (At the crack of dawn) \n暗夜不再 破曉時分 \nExpress your dream grow with our song (and the dream goes